How to Use This Manifest

Every agent fetches this manifest before doing any work.


Locate the document needed and confirm its status.
Fetch the document using the raw URL listed below.
Confirm the fetch before beginning any work.
Locked documents take authority over drafts.
Deprecated documents have no canonical authority.
If a fetch fails, stop and report it. Do not fall back to memory.



Fetch Protocol Note

All document URLs in this manifest use raw GitHub URLs. Fetch each
document directly using the raw URL listed below.

GitHub CDN caching is inconsistent regardless of URL format — both
raw and blob URLs can serve stale content. After fetching any
document, verify it is current by checking the last entry or section
against known project state. This applies to this manifest itself —
verify the Last updated date against known project state before
trusting document statuses. If any content appears out of date,
do not proceed. Request a manual paste from the designer instead.
Manual paste is authoritative. Never fall back to memory.

Use bash_tool with curl for all GitHub raw URL fetches —
web_fetch serves stale CDN content regardless of URL format.
curl is the reliable path.


